   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1861_01_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Moormann_Co_Batavia_1.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>HONG KONG P.O. By mail via Singapore<lb/> &amp; Shanghai<lb/> Mr.<lb/> L Kniffler
                &amp; C<lb/> Nagasaki<lb/> E. Moormann &amp; Co<lb/>Batavia Japan ⟨1861<lb/> Batavia
                16 Jan. 1861<lb/>E. Moormann &amp; Co<lb/>R[eceived] 20 March“Syrian”<lb/> 25/3⟩</p>
         <pb facs="1861_01_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Moormann_Co_Batavia_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>Batavia 16th Jan. 1861<lb/> Mr.<lb/>L. Kniffler &amp; C<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/> We
                acknowledge the pleasant <lb/>receipt of your esteemed letter from 1st
                Dec.,<lb/>from which we have received your sales invoice <lb/>for 1 box of rhino
                horns with a commission of $ 1,023,75„,<lb/> for which we credited for you the
                remittance given to us for the same amount<lb/> with the local Messrs. Pandel &amp;
                Stiehaus<lb/> under the usual caveats. <lb/>Once we receive some more of this
                article,<lb/> we will be kindly willing to let you have fresh<lb/> consignations of
                these as well as<lb/>of other articles which have a chance of the prospect of profit
                &amp; we will <lb/>confer further in this regard with your <lb/>esteemed house.
                <lb/>In the meantime we<lb/> take our leave from you<lb/> with devoted respect <lb/>
                pp E Moormann Co<lb/>C Sonderegger </p>
         <pb facs="1861_01_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Moormann_Co_Batavia_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1861_01_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Moormann_Co_Batavia_4.tif" n="4"/>
      </body>
   </text>
